@node "Einführung" "What is MailEd ?"
 MailEd is a editor especially for writing E-Mails. Overall, where you try to
write your email- letters with a normal text- editor with several script-files
, there you can start directly with MailEd.

MailEd is no universal editor, he`s directly designed for writing Email, but
that he can do without time intensive configuration.

With MailEd you can concentrate yourself onto the content of your mails and
not onto your keyboard- shortcuts.

@{"What can MailEd do ?" link "WhatcanMailEdDo" 0}
@endnode

@node "Systemrequiements" "System requirements"
MailEd runs from OS 2.0 on every Amiga in every solution on every graphic
board with every font :-)

External Librarys: ReqTools.library >= V38 (Copyright Nico Francis)
@endnode

@node "Installation" "Installation & Start"
1-Copy the the program to where ever you like. If you want to use a other
language, copy the affected catalogs/<language>- directory- path in the same
dir as Mailed itself.

2-Make shure that you have the ReqTools-Library installed (Available e.g. from
AmiNet)

3-Use the MailEd- Program as Ext. Editor in your Mail- Program.

That`s it :-)


Optional Parameters:

There are a few parameters, which can be used from CLI or as ToolType, when
you start MailEd from Workbench.

 @{b}MailEd File,Margin/N/K,Size/N/K,TabSize/N/K,Tabs/S,QuoteSign/K@{ub}


@{b}File:@{ub} The file you want to edit.

@{b}Margin:@{ub} Left Margin: This parameter will only be used during Printing
   @{b}Default:@{ub} 0: Range 0-30

@{b}Size:@{ub} This is the complete line- Length, that means row size + left
Margin(Border) This length is used for the word- wrapping
   @{b}Default:@{ub} 79: Range 40-79

@{b}TabSize:@{ub} Defines the tabsize
   @{b}Default:@{ub} 5 Range 1-15

@{b}Boxmode:@{ub} If this switch is set, TABs will be saved as TABs
   @{b}Default:@{ub} Tabs will be saved as SPACEs

@{b}QuoteSign:@{ub} Which this the Quote- Sign for Reply- Messages can be defined This
is used for the "Reply-Paragraphs"- Recocnition
  @{b} Default:@{ub} ">"
@endnode

