@node "WhatcanMailEdDo" "What is Mailed able to do ?"


 @{" automatic Functions " link "automaticFunctions" 0} This MailEd does by its own
 @{" Keys                " link "Keys" 0} The keyboard- functions
 @{" Menus               " link "Menus" 0} The Menuitems
 @{" Statusline          " link "StatusLine" 0} The status-line
 @{" Mouse               " link "Mouse" 0} The left mousebutton
@endnode

@node "automaticFunctions" "automatic Functions"
MailEd is a Text- Editor especially for EMail- Text.

He works as a normal Word- Processor, the text will be formatted in
paragraphs, where also the quoted areas will be handed as several paragraphs.

MailEd also controls the conjuction for the quoted areas during formating.

The several fontstyles (Bold, Italic and Underline) will be shown as Wysiwyg.

And the best: The whole Layout (Paragraphs and Styles) can be easely
transfered via EMail to somebody else, uneffected from Quoting and so, and the
other one can work further will this formatting without loosing the layout.

But nevertheless: The whole text is always fully normal ASCII- Text and can be
read and further used by every other program!
@endnode

@node "Keys" "Keys"

       @{b}RETURN@{ub}      : Adds a new line behind the current
      @{b} DEL@{ub},
       @{b}BackSpace@{ub}   : As usual
       @{b}ESC@{ub}         : Save the text, if changed, with request under the
original filename
       @{b}TAB@{ub}         : Add blanks up to the next TAB- Position
       @{b}F1@{ub}          : Toggle Blockmode on/off
      @{b} DEL@{ub}         : Cuts the current block

@{b}Shift@{ub}+ @{b}CursorUp@{ub}    : Page down
       @{b}CursorDown@{ub}  : Page up
       @{b}RETURN@{ub}      : splits the current line on the cursor postion
       @{b}DEL@{ub}         : Delete current line
       @{b}CursorRight@{ub} : Top of Line
       @{b}CursorLeft@{ub}  : End of Line
       @{b}ESC@{ub}         : Saves without request
       @{b}TAB@{ub}         : Back to last Tab- Position
      @{b} SPACE@{ub}       : Toggle Low/Uppercase

@{b}CTRL@{ub}+  @{b}Y@{ub}           : Deletes current line (Best regards to W*rdstar)
       @{b}F@{ub}           : Formating current Line+ cursor 1 line down
       @{b}DEL@{ub}         : Deletes current line (Best regards to G*ldEd and to Matt
:-)

@{b}ALT@{ub}+   @{b}CursorLeft@{ub},
       @{b}CursorRight@{ub} : last/next word
       @{b}Space@{ub}       : HardBlank
@endnode

