@node "Mouse" "Mouse"
Hold LMB: Moving of the cursor

DoubleClick LMB: Switch Blockmode on/off
@endnode

@node "Project" "Project"
 @{b}Open@{ub}    : Open a new file
 @{b}Save@{ub}    : Save the file
 @{b}save  As@{ub}: Saves under new name
 @{b}Info@{ub}    : Shows the Info- Requester
 @{b}Print@{ub}   : Prints the file
 @{b}Quit@{ub}    : What do you think?
@endnode

@node "Edit" "Edit"
Cut:       Cuts the marked block into the buffer

Copy:      Copies the marked block into the buffer

Paste:     Inserts the buffer before the actual line

WriteFile: Writes the actual block optional with or without quoting in a file

Loadfile:  Inserts a file before the actual line
@endnode

@node "Style" "Style"
Here you can select the possible Fontstyles for the word, which is just the
cursor.

The selected style stays active, until a  non-alphanummeric character is keyed
in.

The actual Style is also shown in the statusline.

Because of the restriction for EMail, you can only style single words, not
whole paragraphs.



@endnode

@node "PGP" "PGP"
Investigate:

 The actual text (without quotes) will be saved in T: and PGP will be started
to investigate the
 content. Useful to extract keys or check signs.

Encrypt:
 PGP will try to encrypt the original. MailEd then loads the result.
@endnode

@node "Preferences" "Preferences"
 @{b}Window@{ub}
  @{" Screen & Fonts" link "Screen" 0}
  @{" Several       " link "Several" 0}
@endnode

@node "Screen" "Window"

 @{b}Screen@{ub} : Screenmode- Select
 @{b}Font@{ub}   : Choosing the prefered Font
@endnode

@node "Several" "Several"
 @{b}Cookie-File@{ub}

Here you select the file with your cookies, where MailEd can append the actual
block as new cookie

 @{b}Switches@{ub}

   @{b}XPFormat@{ub}

If selected, Mailed save its files with two blanks in the end of a line, which
is the the same format as the popular german program CrossPoint (C. Peter
Mandella) use.

   @{b}NewLookMenu@{ub}

With this the menus will be shown with another colorstyle (under OS3.0).
Useful for graphicboards.

   @{b}Special-Return@{ub}

If selected, "RETURN" will add a new line before the actual, not behind, if
the cursor is on the first character in the line.

   @{b}FullQuote@{ub}

If selected, a whole quoted line will be shown in another color, otherways
only the quote-signs in the beginning.

   @{b}ZCBytes@{ub}

If set, MailEd shows in the Statusline not the real filesize (with only CR),
but the size if <CR>+>LF> would be in the end of each line. This format is
common in some PC-based Networks.

 @{b}Default@{ub}

If you`ve selected a screenmode which can`t be displayed on your Monitor, with
this Shortcut MailEd jumps back to the system- screen-default.
@endnode

@node "Extras" "Extras"
Collect Cookie:

When you`ve found a funny cookie, you can select it as a block and by using
this Menuitem, the cookie area will append to your cookie-file. Leading Quotes
will be suppressed during save.
@endnode

@node "StatusLine" "Status line"
Here the length of the current file, the number of lines, the percentage of
quoted text, the cursorposition and the statusflags will be shown.

Statusflags:

File changed: .= unchanged, C = changed

XPFormat: .= normal format, X: XP-Format

Fontstyle: .=Normal B=Bold U=Underline I=Italic
@endnode

@node "WhatIsMissing" "What is missing"
 7-Bit character set
 ROT13
 Cutting the Footer
 UUDecode
 Clipboard- Support
 Write-protection for some Textareas (i.e. uuencoded binarys)
@endnode

